description:
ARCHITECTURAL FIX: UserStorage DO was implemented with HTTP routes in fetch() handler. Should use Workers RPC instead.

**Current (wrong):**
```typescript
async fetch(request: Request) {
  if (path === '/functions/:id/versions') {
    return new Response(JSON.stringify(await this.listVersions(id)))
  }
}
```

**Should be (Workers RPC):**
```typescript
class UserStorage extends DurableObject {
  async listFunctionVersions(functionId: string): Promise<string[]> {
    // Direct RPC method - no HTTP
  }
}

// Caller:
const stub = env.USER_STORAGE.get(id)
const versions = await stub.listFunctionVersions('my-func')
```

**Benefits of RPC:**
- No HTTP serialization overhead
- Type-safe method calls
- capnproto zero-copy performance
- Cleaner code

**Files to change:**
1. src/do/user-storage.ts - Convert HTTP routes to RPC methods
2. src/core/user-storage-client.ts - Update client to use RPC calls instead of fetch
3. Remove fetch() handler HTTP routing logic

**Reference:** https://developers.cloudflare.com/durable-objects/api/rpc/
